article.headline: Belmont 78, North Florida 72
article.story: JACKSONVILLE, Fla. (AP) -- Josh Goodwin scored 17 points to help Belmont defeat North Florida 78 to 72 Saturday. Belmont (5-7, 3-2) shot 61 percent for the game, while Justin Hare added 16 points and Andy Wicke 12 for the Bruins. Belmont was leading with 37 to 34 at the end of the first half. The Bruins' center Boomer Herndon scored five straight points and finished with 13 points. North Florida's Rashad Williams scored 25 points and 12 rebounds. Chris Timberlake added 15 points for the Ospreys (3-9, 0-5), who shot 39 percent for the game.
